The suspect turned himself into Sunnyside police and told officers he was obeying orders from a mysterious evil spirit. JOHANNESBURG - A Pretoria man accused of killing his mother has told police that an evil spirit made him commit the crime. Her body was found in the man's flat on Wednesday night; she had been stabbed multiple times. The suspect turned himself into Sunnyside police and told officers he was obeying orders from a mysterious evil spirit. Police spokesperson Daniel Mavimbela said: “As a result, myself and some of the members who attended the scene have arranged that we undergo a debriefing session with our station’s employee health and wellness unit as soon as possible as a precautionary measure.”